       The GRASS XDRIVER can be used to display GRASS maps in X11 environment.

UUssaaggee iinn ddeettaaiillss
                     Set the map size for the XDRIVER:
                     export   GRASS_WIDTH=xxx      (default   is  640)  export
                     GRASS_HEIGHT=yyy    (default is 480)

                     If "export" command is not accepted by  your  shell,  use
                     "setenv"   instead:   setenv   GRASS_WIDTH   xxx   setenv
                     GRASS_HEIGHT yyy

                     Further variables:
                     XDRIVER_LEFT

                       defines the left position of GRASS monitor XDRIVER_TOP

                       define the upper position of GRASS monitor
       To control the XDRIVER, use the d.mon module.


       The maximum color depth depends on the current X Server settings.

